Brian Wenzel https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brian_Wenzel 0 Brian Thomas Wenzel (born 24 May 1929 in Adelaide, South Australia) is an Australian Logie Award winning character actor and comedian. He has been in the entertainment business for 73 years, including circus, stage, television and film;(including made for TV movies and theatrical release films). However, he remains most famous for his long-running role as Frank Gilroy, an original character on television program A Country Practice. from its inception pilot in November 1981 until the series conclusion in 1993, the only original along with Shane Porteous to appear the duration of the series run, and at the time one of the longest roles on Australian television. He was a cast member of Rove McManus's show Rove Live in 2009.
